ique (Concerto de Qu\u00e9bec, 1943)\n* Piano Concerto No. 4 (1947)\n| [[Romantic music|Romantic]]\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Willem|Andriessen}} || 1887 || 1964 || Dutch || \n|\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Samuel|Barber}} || 1910 || 1981 || American ||\n* Concerto for Piano and Orchestra op.38 (1962)\n* Nocturne for Piano (Homage to John Field), Op. 33\n* Sonata for Piano (Op. 26, 1949)\n| \n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|B\u00e9la|Bart\u00f3k}} || 1881 || 1945 || Hungarian ||\n* [[Mikrokosmos (B\u00e9la Bart\u00f3k)|Mikrokosmos, Sz. 107, BB 105]]\n* [[Out of Doors (Bart\u00f3k)|Out of Doors, Sz. 81, BB 89]]\n* [[Romanian Folk Dances|Romanian Folk Dances, Sz. 56, BB 68]]\n* [[Allegro barbaro (Bart\u00f3k)|Allegro barbaro, Sz. 49, BB 63]]\n| Folksong-influenced, Centric, [[Mode (music)|Modal]], Polymodal/[[Polytonality|Polytonal]] \n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Arnold|Bax}} || 1883 || 1953 || English || \n* Piano Sonata No. 1 (1910, 1917\u20131920)\n* Piano Sonata No. 2 (1919)\n* [[Piano Sonata in E-flat (Bax)|Piano Sonata in E-flat]] (1921)\n* Piano Sonata No. 3 (1926)\n* Piano Sonata No. 4 (1932)\n| [[Romantic music|Romantic]], [[Impressionist music|Impressionist]] \n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Emile-Robert|Blanchet}} || 1877 || 1943 || Swiss || \n| \n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n\n| {{sortname|York|Bowen}} || 1884 || 1961 || English || \n| [[Romantic music|Romantic]] \n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Frank|Bridge}} || 1879 || 1941 || English || \n| Late-Romantic, hints of Second Viennese School\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Ferruccio|Busoni}} || 1866 || 1924 || Italian || \n* ''[[Fantasia contrappuntistica]]'' (1910)\n| Mature works of indeterminate key; Late in career, [[Neoclassicism (music)|neoclassical]]\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Alfredo|Casella}} || 1883 || 1947 || Italian || \n|\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|C\u00e9cile|Chaminade}} || 1857 || 1944 || French || \n| \n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Mikalojus Konstantinas|\u010