essionist]] and exotic influences \n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Ignacy Jan|Paderewski}} || 1860 || 1941 || Polish || \n|\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Jacobo|Palm}} || 1887 || 1982 || Cura\u00e7ao-born || \n|\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|John|Palm}} || 1885 || 1925 || Cura\u00e7ao-born || \n|\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Rudolph|Palm}} || 1880 || 1950 || Cura\u00e7ao-born || \n|\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Selim|Palmgren}} || 1878 || 1951 || Finnish || \n|\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Isidor|Philipp}} || 1863 || 1958 || French, Hungarian || \n|\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Francis|Poulenc}} || 1899 || 1963 || French || \n|\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Sergei|Prokofiev}} || 1891 || 1953 || Russian || \n* [[Piano Sonata No. 6 (Prokofiev)|Sonata No. 6 in A major, Op. 82]] (1940)\n* [[Piano Sonata No. 7 (Prokofiev)|Sonata No. 7 in B-flat major, Op. 83]] (1942)\n* [[Piano Sonata No. 8 (Prokofiev)|Sonata No. 8 in B-flat major, Op. 84]] (1944)\n* [[Visions fugitives|Visions fugitives, Op. 22]] (1915\u20131917)\n* [[Toccata (Prokofiev)|Toccata in D minor, Op. 11]] (1912)\n|\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Sergei|Rachmaninoff}} || 1873 || 1943 || Russian || \n* [[Piano Sonata No. 1 (Rachmaninoff)|Sonata No. 1 in D minor, Op. 28]] (1908)\n* [[Piano Sonata No. 2 (Rachmaninoff)|Sonata No. 2 in B-flat minor, Op. 36]] (1914)\n* [[Six moments musicaux (Rachmaninoff)|Six moments musicaux, Op. 16]] (1897)\n| [[Romantic music|Romantic]]\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Maurice|Ravel}} || 1875 || 1937 || French || \n* ''[[Gaspard de la nuit]]'' (1908)\n* ''[[Le tombeau de Couperin]]'' (1914\u20131917)\n* ''[[Jeux d'eau (Ravel)|Jeux d'eau]]'' (1901)\n| [[Impressionist music|Impressionist]]; sometimes jazz-influenced\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Vladimir|Rebikov}} || 1866 || 1920 || Russian || \n| [[Impressionist music|Impressionist]], [[Romantic music|Romantic]]\n|-valign=\"top\"\n\n| {{sortname|Emmanuel|Rhen\u00e9-Baton|Rhen\u00e9-Baton}