tm\n | title = Reading Comprehension \u2013 Rock 'N Learn\n | accessdate = November 2, 2011\n | publisher = Rock 'N Learn\n}}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"LearnMath\">\n{{cite AV media\n | date = November 25, 2009\n | title = Learn Math: Money & Making Change\n | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_yMcZFXmN-A\n | work = YouTube\n | medium = trailer\n | publisher = Rock 'N Learn\n}}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"fallout1\">\n{{ cite AV media\n | date = January 24, 2011\n | title = Fallout: Nuka Break \u2013 Fan Film\n | work = YouTube\n | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q9UwlAAnlmg\n | author = Wayside Creations\n | time = 15:01\n}}\n</ref>\n<ref name=\"fallout2\">{{cite web\n |url          = http://planetfallout.gamespy.com/articles/news/2070/Fallout-Nuka-Break-Released\n |title        = Fallout: Nuka Break Released\n |date         = January 24, 2011\n |publisher    = [[GameSpy]]\n |access-date  = November 2, 2011\n |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20110825053235/http://planetfallout.gamespy.com/articles/news/2070/Fallout-Nuka-Break-Released\n |archive-date = August 25, 2011\n |url-status   = dead\n |df           = mdy-all\n}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Free! - Eternal Summer\">\n{{cite web\n | last = Ressler\n | first = Karen\n | url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-11-14/free-eternal-summer-english-dub-casts-vic-mignogna-as-rin/.81030\n | title = Free Eternal Summer English Dub Casts Vic Mignogna as Rin\n | publisher = [[Anime News Network]]\n | date = November 14, 2014\n | access-date = October 18, 2019\n}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{ANN|people|2516}}\n* {{AnimeCons name|id=517|name=Vic Mignogna}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* [http://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/Vic-Mignogna/ Vic Mignogna] at Behind The Voice Actors\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mignogna, Vic}}\n[[Category:1960s births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male singers]]\n[[Category:American male video game actors]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Liberty University alumni]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Houston]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Philadelphia]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Houston]]\n[[Category:People from Greensburg, Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:People from Westmoreland County, Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Singers from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Singers from Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Singers from Texas]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from California]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from Texas]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century American singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century male singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American voice actor and musician}}\n{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vic Mignogna\n| image              = Vic Mignogna by Gage Skidmore 3.jpg\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = Mignogna in 2017\n| birth_name         = Victor Joseph Mignogna <!-- this is confirmed on his professional resume -->\n| birth_date         = {{birth based on age as of date |56|2019|08|03}} <!-- Exact date is excluded due to [[WP:BLPPRIVACY]]. See talk page. -->\n| birth_place        = [[Greensburg, Pennsylvania|Greensburg]], [[Pennsylvania]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n*Voice actor\n*musician\n}}\n| years_active       = 1999\u2013present\n| home_town          = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.<ref name=\"laweekly\"/>\n| website            = {{Official URL}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed              = yes\n| background         = solo_singer\n| instrument         = {{flatlist|\n* Piano\n* vocals\n}}\n| genre              = {{flatlist|\n* Pop\n* Christian & Gospel}}<!-- iTunes classifications -->\n| years_active = 1989\u2013present{{#tag:ref|1999 was the year that Mignogna began voice acting for anime dubs for television shows and videos. He has been composing and producing music since ''[[DC Talk]]''{{'}}s album in 1989, and appeared on television in 1993 as a contestant on ''[[Star Search]]''.|group=N}}\n }}\n}}\n\n<!-- Please do not add his birth date without an official, reliable source to back up your claim. See Wikipedia:Biographies of Living Persons. -->\n'''Victor Joseph Mignogna''' ({{IPAc-en|m|\u026a|n|\u02c8|j|\u0252|n|\u0259}}; born 1962 or 1963)<ref name=\"dallas 2019-08-03\"/><!-- see [[WP:BLPPRIVACY]] --> is an [[United States|American]] [[voice actor]] and [[musician]] known for his voice-over work in the English dubs of Japanese [[anime]] shows, the most notable being [[Edward Elric]] from the ''[[Fullmetal Alchemist]]'' series, for which he earned the [[American Anime Awards|American Anime Award]] for Best Actor in 2007. Other notable animation roles include [[Broly]] from the ''[[Dragon Ball]]'' films, [[Tamaki Suoh]] in ''[[Ouran High School Host Club]]'', [[Fai D. Flowright]] in ''[[Tsubasa: Reservoir Chronicle]]'', [[Dark Mousy|Dark]] in ''[[D.N.Angel]]'', [[Kurz Weber]] in the ''[[Full Metal Panic!]]'' series, [[Zero Kiryu|Zero]] and [[Ichiru Kiryu]] in the ''[[Vampire Knight]]'' series, [[List of Digimon Fusion characters#Fusion Fighters|Christopher Aonuma]] in ''[[Digimon Fusion]]'', [[List of Naruto characters#Nagato|Nagato]] and [[#Obito Uchiha|Obito Uchiha]] in ''[[Naruto Shippuden]]'', [[Ikkaku Madarame]] in ''[[Bleach (anime)|Bleach]]'', [[List of RWBY characters#Qrow|Qrow Branwen]] in ''[[RWBY]]'', and [[Matt Ishida]] in ''[[Digimon Adventure tri.]]'' In video games, he is the voice of [[E-123 Omega]] in the ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog]]'' series and [[List of Persona 3 characters#Junpei Iori|Junpei Iori]] from ''[[Persona 3]]''. In live-action work, he has participated in several [[Star Trek fan productions|''Star Trek'' fan productions]], including ''[[Star Trek Continues]]'', where he plays Captain [[James T. Kirk]]. Mignogna has an official fanclub called Risembool Rangers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.risemboolrangers.com/about-the-fan-club.html|title=ABOUT THE FAN CLUB|website=Risembool Rangers' Fan Page|language=en|access-date=2019-09-24}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2019, studios [[Funimation]] and [[Rooster Teeth]] cut ties with Mignogna after a number of [[sexual harassment]] allegations surfaced. Mignogna has denied the allegations and filed a lawsuit against Funimation and several individuals in April 2019 alleging [[defamation]] and [[tortious interference]].\n\n==Early life==\nMignogna was born in [[Greensburg, Pennsylvania|Greensburg]], [[Pennsylvania]], to Barb Myers.<ref name=\"elderkin\">{{Cite web|url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/one-of-anime-s-biggest-voices-accused-of-sexual-harassm-1832390505|title=One of Anime's Biggest Voices Accused of Sexual Harassment|last=Elderkin|first=Beth|website=[[io9]]|access-date=2019-02-20|date=February 19, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"risembool\" /> He graduated from [[Liberty University]] with a degree in television and film production,<ref name=\"pro_resume\" /><ref>{{cite news |url=https://digitalcommons.liberty.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1014&context=paper_88_89 | title=''Annie'': A review: Musical is 'upbeat,... entertaining' |first1=Megan |last1=Bearder |first2=Allison | last2=Troy |newspaper=[[Liberty University|The Liberty Champion]] |volume=6 |issue=5 | date=March 1, 1989 |pages=1, 4 | quote=As Rooster, Vic Mignogna, a drama graduate with much experience, could easily steal the show. }}</ref> and taught English and speech at Trinity Christian Academy in [[Jacksonville, Florida|Jacksonville]], [[Florida]].<ref name=\"ann 2019-07-29 fan interactions\">{{Cite news|first=Lynzee|last=Loveridge|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-07-29/mignogna-deposition-fan-interactions-and-the-affidavits/.149271|title=Mignogna Deposition: Fan Interactions and The Affidavits|work=[[Anime News Network]] | date=2019-07-29 | accessdate=2019-07-30}}</ref> Mignogna helped produce and arrange some of the songs on [[DC Talk]]'s [[DC Talk (album)|eponymous first album]].<ref name=\"risembool\"/><ref name=\"pro_resume\"/><ref name=\"chronicle_bio\"/> He was a summer seasonal officer with the [[Ocean City Police Department]].<ref name=\"pro_resume\"/> In 1990, Mignogna moved to [[Houston, Texas|Houston]], [[Texas]], where he was a film and video production instructor at [[The Art Institute of Houston]].<ref name=\"chronicle_bio\"/> In 1993, he was a contestant on American television talent show ''[[Star Search]]'', on which he sang \"Worth Waiting For\".<ref name=\"last.fm\"/>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:VicMignognaJune2011.jpg|thumb|Mignogna at a comic expo in Calgary, Canada, June 2011]]\n\nWhile working in video production with [[John Gremillion]] in Houston, Mignogna got involved in [[voice acting]] at [[ADV Films]].<ref name=\"risembool\"/><ref name=\"chronicle_bio\"/> He made his debut as [[Vega (Street Fighter)|Vega]] in the video game-based [[anime]] series ''[[Street Fighter II V]]''.<ref name=\"laweekly\">{{cite web | url=http://blogs.laweekly.com/arts/2009/05/fullmetal_trekkie_voice_actor.php | title=Fullmetal Trekkie: Voice Actor Vic Mignogna to Direct Star Trek: Phase II Episode | work=[[LA Weekly]] | date=May 28, 2009 | last=Ohanesian | first=Liz | access-date=June 18, 2012 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212160545/http://blogs.laweekly.com/arts/2009/05/fullmetal_trekkie_voice_actor.php | archive-date=December 12, 2013 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"risembool\"/><ref name=\"otakureview\">{{cite web |last1=McCarthy |first1=Rebecca |title=An Interview with Vic Mignogna |url=https://www.otakunews.com/us/Article/1882/an-interview-with-vic-mignogna |website=Otaku News |accessdate=October 18, 2019 |language=en |date=January 18, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"gawl\">At his panel in [[Anime Expo]] 2006, Mignogna said his first starring role was Gawl in ''[[Generator Gawl]]''.</ref><ref name=\"heavymetal\">{{cite web | url=http://totalscifionline.com/interviews/3975-vic-mignogna-heavy-metal | title=Vic Mignogna: Heavy Metal | publisher=[[Dreamwatch|TotalSciFi online]] | date=September 15, 2009 | access-date=January 23, 2012 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110705014231/http://totalscifionline.com/interviews/3975-vic-mignogna-heavy-metal | archive-date=July 5, 2011 | url-status=dead | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Mignogna started attending anime conventions, where he contacted [[Funimation]] and landed the voice role of [[Broly]] in the ''[[Dragonball|Dragon Ball]]'' films.<ref name=\"risembool\"/><ref name=\"otakureview\"/>\n\nIn 2007, the [[American Anime Awards]] presented Mignogna with an award for Best Actor for his work on ''[[Fullmetal Alchemist]]''.<ref name=\"Anime Awards\"/><ref name=\"award winners\"/><ref name=\"AutoAS-1\"/> He often gains attention for his role in ''Alchemist'', and he at one point attended between 15 to 25 conventions per year.<ref name=\"laweekly\"/><ref name=\"animecons\"/> One of Mignogna's career goals was \"to record at all of the major places where [[dubbing]] is done\".<ref name=\"bamboo\"/> He said he was \"the first ADV voice actor to record at Funimation in [[Dallas]] and then I was the first to go to [[New York City|New York]]\".<ref name=\"bamboo\"/> He has also recorded in [[Los Angeles]]; he tried out for ''[[Bleach (anime)|Bleach]]'' and received the part of [[Ikkaku Madarame]].<ref name=\"YouTube\"/><ref name=\"LuckyDance\"/> In non-anime productions, he voiced [[List of RWBY characters#Qrow|Qrow Branwen]] in [[Rooster Teeth|Rooster Teeth's]] web series ''[[RWBY]]''.<ref name=\"rwby rooster teeth\"/>\n\nIn addition to voice acting, Mignogna has been involved in production for music, sound and video.<ref name=\"VicsWorld\"/><ref name=\"Video Production\"/> He has produced hundreds of [[jingle]]s for commercials,<ref name=\"bamboo\"/> and he was a worship leader with Houston's First Baptist Church.<ref name=\"tangles\">{{cite web|url=http://beneaththetangles.com/2013/06/26/interview-with-voice-actor-vic-mignogna/ |title=Interview with Voice Actor Vic Mignogna &#124; |publisher=Beneaththetangles.com |date=June 26, 2013 |accessdate=August 26, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"chronicle_bio\"/> Mignogna has sung the [[The Star-Spangled Banner|U.S. national anthem]] at several [[Houston Astros]] baseball games.<ref name=\"chronicle_bio\"/> As a musician, he has released several [[studio album|albums]], some of which feature English [[cover version]]s of anime songs from shows including ''[[One Piece]]'' and the ''Dragon Ball'' series. He also handled some of the ADR direction for the English dub of ''[[Claymore (manga)|Claymore]]'', in which he voices Rigaldo.\n\nMignogna has been involved with several [[fan production]]s, including ''Fullmetal Fantasy''<ref name=\"bamboo\"/> and ''[[Star Trek: New Voyages|Star Trek: Phase II]]''. In the latter series, he co-directed the episode \"Enemy: Starfleet\" and played the [[Andorian]] Captain. He directed \"KITUMBA\" and played Malkthon the [[Klingon]], and was slated to direct the episode \"Mindsifter\".<ref name=\"laweekly\"/><ref name=\"heavymetal\"/><ref name=\"StarTrek\"/> In 2012, Mignogna worked with the [[Star Trek fan productions|Starship Farragut]] production group. He directed and starred as Captain [[James T. Kirk]] in their web series ''[[Star Trek Continues]]''.<ref name=\"mcmexpo2012_laura\"/><ref name=\"farragut\">{{cite press release | url=http://www.starshipfarragut.com/the-news/FF_Press_Release-Addl_Members_and_New_Studio-FINAL.pdf | title=Farragut Films Adds to Management Team and Secures Largest Studio of Trek Sets | work=Farragut Films | date=December 29, 2011 | accessdate=February 3, 2012 |url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120417002150/http://www.starshipfarragut.com/the-news/FF_Press_Release-Addl_Members_and_New_Studio-FINAL.pdf |archive-date=April 17, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"farragut2\">{{cite web | url=http://www.starshipfarragut.com/2012_additions.php | title=Starship Farragut: New Team Members and Studio | work=Farragut Films | accessdate=February 3, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"startrekcontinues\"/> Mignogna has received good reviews for writing, directing, executive-producing and starring in ''[[Star Trek Continues]]'', especially for his portrayal of the character of Kirk, respectfully utilizing [[William Shatner]]'s unique mannerisms and cadence.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Young |first1=Rob |title=Star Trek Continues: A Great Web Series and a Great Homage |url=https://www.cinelinx.com/tv/item/9472-star-trek-continues-a-great-web-series-and-a-great-homage.html |website=cinelinx.com |accessdate=January 31, 2019 |language=en-gb |date=May 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Sexual harassment allegations===\nFollowing the English release of ''[[Dragon Ball Super: Broly]]'', which prominently features Mignogna's vocal work, accusations of [[sexual harassment]] began to surface against Mignogna on [[Twitter]], with some allegations dating as far back as 1989.<ref name=\"dallas 2019-08-03\">{{cite news | first=Sharon | last=Grisby | url=https://www.dallasnews.com/news/courts/2019/08/03/anime-gets-metoo-moment-clash-dallas-area-voice-actors | title=Anime gets its #MeToo moment in clash between Dallas-area voice actors | work=[[Dallas Morning News]] | date=2019-08-03 | accessdate=2019-08-04}}</ref><ref name=polygon1>{{cite web |last1=Radulovic |first1=Petrana |title=Dragon Ball Super: Broly voice actor responds to sexual harassment, homophobia claims |url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/1/25/18197827/dragon-ball-super-broly-vic-mignogna-harassment-response |website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=2019-02-06 |language=en |date=2019-01-25}}</ref><ref name=newsweek>{{cite web |last1=Martinez |first1=Phillip |title=Vic Mignogna no longer part of 'RWBY' cast amid allegations |url=https://www.newsweek.com/vic-mignogna-rwby-allegations-1318722 |work=[[Newsweek]] |accessdate=2019-02-06 |language=en |date=2019-02-05}}</ref><ref name=\"ann 2019-02-20\">{{cite news|first=Rafael Antonio|last=Pineda|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-02-20/bulma-voice-actress-monica-rial-shares-alleged-inappropriate-encounters-with-vic-mignogna/.143664|title=Bulma Voice Actress Monica Rial Shares Alleged Inappropriate Encounters With Vic Mignogna|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2019-02-20|accessdate=2019-02-20}}</ref> Multiple accounts alleged that Mignogna kissed, [[groping|groped]] and made unwanted comments to fans without their consent, some of whom were underage, using the hashtag \"#KickVic\".<ref name=polygon1/><ref name=newsweek/><ref name=IGN1>{{cite web |last1=Wade |first1=Jesse |title=Dragon Ball voice actor dismissed from RWBY following misconduct allegations |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/02/05/dragon-ball-voice-actor-dismissed-from-rwby-following-misconduct-allegations |website=[[IGN]] |accessdate=2019-02-06 |language=en |date=2019-02-05}}</ref> Voice actresses [[Monica Rial]] and [[Jamie Marchi]] also tweeted their support for those speaking out, and openly alleged being sexually harassed by Mignogna.<ref name=\"dallas 2019-08-03\"/><ref name=\"ann 2019-02-20\"/><ref>Voice actress tweets:\n* {{cite tweet | first=Monica | last=Rial | authorlink=Monica Rial | user=Rialisms | number=1093275331929296897|date=February 7, 2019|title=Dropping in to say this: stop harassing my friends and colleagues. You want the truth? IT HAPPENED TO ME! I had hoped it wouldn\u2019t come to this but here we are. I don\u2019t owe you anything but if it\u2019ll stop it from happening to someone else, then so be it.}}\n* {{cite tweet| first=Monica | last=Rial | authorlink=Monica Rial | user=Rialisms| number=1093283179329400832|date=2019-02-07|title=I am 100% talking about Vic Mignogna. This has nothing to do with him being inappropriate with fans.}}\n* {{cite tweet|first=Jamie | last=Marchi | authorlink=Jamie Marchi |user=marchimark|number=1094020618327150592|date=2019-02-08|title=I stand with the victims. My experience is minor in comparison to many others; however, having realized this wasn't an isolated incident, I felt compelled to share.}}</ref>\n\nOn January 22, 2019, Tammi Denbrow, the executive director of employee relations at [[Sony Pictures]], opened an investigation based on reports made by Rial, two female fans and a former Funimation employee, which concluded on January 29 and resulted in Mignogna's contract termination.<ref name=\"ann 2019-07-29\">{{cite news | first=Lynzee | last=Loveridge | url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-07-29/mignogna-deposition-the-funimation-investigation/.149250 | title=Mignogna Deposition: The Funimation Investigation | work=[[Anime News Network]] | date=2019-07-29 | accessdate=2019-07-30}}</ref> On February 5, Rooster Teeth severed their business relationship with Mignogna, and Funimation recast his role of the Executive in ''[[The Morose Mononokean]]''. Funimation later publicly confirmed they had ended professional ties with Mignogna on February 11.<ref>{{Cite tweet|author=Funimation|authorlink=Funimation |user=FUNimation|number=1095087396209770501|date=2019-02-11|title=Everyone, we wanted to give you an update on the Vic Mignogna situation. Following an investigation, Funimation recast Vic Mignogna in Morose Mononokean Season 2. Funimation will not be engaging Mignogna in future productions.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/2/11/18220550/funimation-fires-vic-mignonga-sexual-harassment|title=Funimation removes voice actor Vic Mignogna from anime, while harassment allegations keep growing|website=Polygon|first=Petrana|last=Radulovic|date=2019-02-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ressler |first1=Karen |title=Vic Mignogna Replaced in Morose Mononokean English Dub Cast (Update) |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-02-05/vic-mignogna-replaced-in-morose-mononokean-english-dub-cast/.143026 |work=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=February 6, 2019 |language=en |date=2019-02-05}}</ref> In response to the controversy, Mignogna categorically denied any accusations of sexual harassment. However, multiple anime conventions withdrew Mignogna from their guest lists.<ref name=IGN1/><ref name=polygon2>{{cite web |last1=Frank |first1=Allegra |title=Rooster Teeth cuts ties with anime voice actor Vic Mignogna amid harassment reports |url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/2/5/18212141/vic-mignogna-fired-rooster-teeth-rwby-sexual-harassment |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=2019-02-06 |language=en |date=2019-02-05}}</ref>\n\nMignogna issued an apology during his panel at [[Bak-Anime]] 2019 and again via Twitter on February 13, 2019.<ref>{{cite news|author=Lynzee Loveridge|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-02-14/dub-voice-actor-vic-mignogna-issues-statement-taking-time-to-recommit-to-god-seeking-help/.143423|title=Dub Voice Actor Vic Mignogna Issues Statement: 'Taking Time to Recommit to God, Seeking Help'|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2019-02-14|accessdate=2019-02-15}}</ref> Since his termination, his fans, who have tagged their support under the hashtag \"#IStandWithVic\", raised over $236,000 on [[GoFundMe]] for legal funds.<ref name=\"dallas 2019-08-03\"/> The GoFundMe account was opened by lawyer Nick Rekieta, who assisted Mignogna in acquiring Ty Beard as his attorney.<ref name=\"dallas 2019-08-03\"/> On February 20, Mignogna confirmed on Twitter that he was pursuing legal action,<ref>{{cite tweet | first=Vic | last=Mignogna | user=vicmignogna | number=1098394938453213185|date=2019-02-20|accessdate=2019-02-21|title=Words cannot express the depth of my gratitude for all the kindness and support that has been shown to me over the last few weeks. I had hoped that my apologies and acknowledgments, both public and private, would be received. But I have now very reluctantly retained a law firm as my last and only recourse to attempt to salvage my reputation and my 20-year career in this industry. A friend expressed a desire to set up a GoFundMe for legal expenses, I approved his kind offer and am so grateful, but I am not managing it, nor will I personally receive any of it. Any surplus will go to the Salvation Army Dallas Domestic Violence Abuse Shelters. I hold no malice towards anyone. I just love my work and the fans, and sincerely wish to continue.}}</ref> and later filed a million-dollar lawsuit against Funimation, Rial, Marchi, and Ron Toye for [[defamation]] and [[tortious interference]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-04-19/vic-mignogna-sues-funimation-jamie-marchi-monica-rial-ronald-toye/.145898|title=Vic Mignogna Sues Funimation, Jamie Marchi, Monica Rial, Ronald Toye|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2019-04-19}}</ref> Funimation filed a response on June 12, 2019, denying Mignogna's allegations.<ref>{{cite news | first=Jennifer | last=Sherman | url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-06-12/funimation-files-response-to-vic-mignogna-lawsuit/.147763 | title=Funimation Files Response to Vic Mignogna's Lawsuit | work=[[Anime News Network]] | date=2019-06-12 | accessdate=2019-07-01}}</ref>\n\nOn June 26, 2019, Mignogna was [[Deposition (law)|deposed]].<ref name=\"dallas 2019-08-03\"/> Funimation then filed an [[anti-SLAPP]] motion on July 1, seeking to dismiss Mignogna's lawsuit.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-03/funimation-files-anti-slapp-motion-to-dismiss-vic-mignogna-lawsuit/.148570|title=Funimation Files anti-SLAPP Motion to Dismiss Vic Mignogna's Lawsuit|work=[[Anime News Network]]|language=en|access-date=2019-07-04}}</ref> Rial, Marchi, and Toye then filed their anti-SLAPP motions on July 19,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-22/monica-rial-ronald-toye-jamie-marchi-also-file-motions-to-dismiss-vic-mignogna-lawsuit/.149217|title=Monica Rial, Ronald Toye, Jamie Marchi Also File Motions to Dismiss Vic Mignogna's Lawsuit|website=Anime News Network|access-date=2019-07-23}}</ref> with ten [[affidavit]]s, including ones from [[Kara Edwards]] and [[Michele Specht]],<ref name=\"ann 2019-07-29 fan interactions\"/><ref name=\"dallas 2019-08-03\"/> as well as several allegations that he had made unwanted advances towards [[Mari Iijima]].<ref>{{Cite news| first=Lynzee|last=Loveridge|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-07-31/former-tekkoshocon-staff-allege-mignogna-harassed-macross-voice-actress-mari-iijima/.149505|title=Former Tekkoshocon Staff Allege Mignogna Harassed Macross Voice Actress Mari Iijima|work=[[Anime News Network]] | date=2019-07-31 | accessdate=2019-07-31}}</ref> On July 30, another affidavit was submitted by the two fans from Funimation's investigation.<ref name=\"dallas 2019-08-03\"/>\n\nMignogna's team was required to file a response by August 30, 2019, but Beard missed the deadline by 27 minutes, citing technical issues, and later submitted a notice to withdraw and resubmit the affidavits on September 2 due to \"defects in form\".<ref name=\"ann 2019-09-04\">{{cite news | first=Lynzee | last=Loveridge | url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-09-04/updated-law-and-disorder-mignogna-counsel-files-rescinds-affidavits-in-3-days/.150613 | title=UPDATED: Law and Disorder: Mignogna's Counsel Files, Rescinds Affidavits in 3 Days | work=[[Anime News Network]] | date=2019-09-04 | accessdate=2019-09-06}}</ref> One of the affidavits included a testimony from [[Chuck Huber]].<ref name=\"ann 2019-09-04\"/> Mignogna's legal team called for [[legal sanction|sanctions]] under suspicion as to whether the affidavits were legally notarized.<ref name=\"ann 2019-09-04\"/> As a result, Mignogna received a court order to appear at a hearing set for September 6 intended for considering the defendants' anti-SLAPP motions,<ref name=\"dallas 2019-08-03\"/><ref name=\"ann 2019-09-05\">{{cite news | first=Lynzee | last=Loveridge | url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-09-05/mignogna-receives-court-order-to-appear-at-friday-hearing/.150790 | title=Mignogna Receives Court Order to Appear at Friday Hearing | work=[[Anime News Network]] | date=2019-09-05 | accessdate=2019-09-06}}</ref> but he did not attend. During the hearing, seven of the twelve cases, particularly against Marchi, were dismissed and Mignogna was required to pay all of her legal fees, with another ruling scheduled in thirty days.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Lynzee|last=Loveridge|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-09-06/mignogna-civil-case-against-voice-actress-jamie-marchi-dismissed/.150828|title=Mignogna's Civil Case Against Voice Actress Jamie Marchi Dismissed|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2019-09-06|access-date=2019-09-07}}</ref><ref name=\"dallas 2019-09-06\">{{cite news | first=Sharon | last=Grisby | url=https://www.dallasnews.com/opinion/commentary/2019/09/06/in-animes-metoo-moment-vic-mignogna-a-no-show-at-tarrant-county-hearing-and-his-case-is-mostly-an-unholy-mess// | title=In anime's #MeToo moment, Vic Mignogna a no-show at Tarrant County hearing and his case is mostly an unholy mess | work=[[Dallas Morning News]] | date=2019-09-06 | accessdate=2019-09-07}}</ref> On September 17, Judge John Chupp ordered both legal teams to [[mediation|mediate]] by October 3 and would rule on all outstanding orders if the mediation is unsuccessful.<ref name=\"dallas 2019-09-17\">{{Cite web| first=Sharon | last=Grisby | url=https://www.dallasnews.com/news/2019/09/17/latest-in-anime-s-metoo-moment-tarrant-county-judge-orders-mediation-and-shares-threats-of-violence-in-vic-mignogna-lawsuit/|title=Latest in anime's #MeToo moment: Tarrant County judge orders mediation and shares threats of violence in Vic Mignogna lawsuit|date=2019-09-17|work=[[Dallas Morning News]]|access-date=2019-09-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|first=Lynzee|last=Loveridge|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-09-17/judge-orders-mignogna-remaining-defendants-to-mediate-before-october-3/.151233|title=Judge Orders Mignogna, Remaining Defendants to Mediate Before October 3|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2019-09-17|access-date=2019-09-17}}</ref> On October 4, Judge Chupp announced that the remaining cases had been dismissed.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.dallasnews.com/opinion/commentary/2019/10/04/anime-voice-actor-vic-mignogna-loses-big-judge-drops-final-claims-dallas-area-studio-colleagues-defamed/ |title=Anime voice actor Vic Mignogna loses big as judge drops final claims that Dallas-area studio and colleagues defamed him |newspaper=The Dallas Morning News|date=2019-10-04}}</ref> Mignogna filed an appeal on October 24, with a hearing set for November 21.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Rafael Antonio|last=Pineda|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-10-30/monica-rial-ron-toye-jamie-marchi-funimation-file-motion-to-dismiss-vic-mignogna-appeal/.152791|title=Monica Rial, Ron Toye, Jamie Marchi, Funimation File Motion to Dismiss Vic Mignogna's Appeal|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2019-10-30|access-date=2019-10-30}}</ref> Judge Chupp later ruled that Mignogna was required to pay $223,042.42 for the defendants' attorney fees.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Jennifer|last=Sherman|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-27/judge-rules-vic-mignogna-must-pay-usd238042-to-defendants-in-lawsuit/.153749|title=Judge Rules Vic Mignogna Must Pay US$238,042 to Defendants in Lawsuit|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2019-11-27|access-date=2019-11-27}}</ref> On October 24, Beard filed for an appeal with the appellate court.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scribd.com/document/432033434/Vic-Mignogna-vs-Funimation-Jamie-Marchi-Monica-Rial-and-Ron-Toye-Notice-of-Appeal |title=Vic Mignogna vs Funimation, Jamie Marchi, Monica Rial and Ron Toye - Notice of Appeal {{!}} Lawsuit {{!}} Courts|website=Scribd|language=en|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref> On October 24, Lemoine filed a motion to dismiss the appeal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-27/judge-rules-vic-mignogna-must-pay-usd238042-to-defendants-in-lawsuit/.153749|title=Judge Rules Vic Mignogna Must Pay US$238,042 to Defendants in Lawsuit|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref> On December 11, Judge Chupp denied the motion to dismiss appeals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://boundingintocomics.com/2019/12/17/vic-mignogna-to-move-forward-with-appeals-process-as-defendants-motion-to-dismiss-is-denied/|title=Vic Mignogna to Move Forward with Appeals Process as Defendant's Motion to Dismiss is Denied|last=Baculi|first=Spencer|date=2019-12-17|website=Bounding Into Comics|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nMignogna was in a relationship with actress [[Michele Specht]] from 2006 to May 2018.<ref name=\"elderkin\" />\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Anime===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width=100%;\"\n|+ List of dubbing performances in anime\n|-\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Year\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Role\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Notes\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Source\n|-\n| 1999 || ''[[Street Fighter II V]]'' || [[Vega (Street Fighter)|Vega]] || ADV dub, debut role || <ref name=\"laweekly\"/><ref name=\"risembool\"/><ref name=\"way jeng\"/>\n|-\n| 1999 || ''[[Martian Successor Nadesico]]'' || Ikeda || Episode 19 || <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.crystalacids.com/database/title/419/martian-successor-nadesico/fullcast/ | title=Full Cast \u2013 Martian Successor Nadesico (TV) (episodes 1 to 26) | publisher=CrystalAcids.com | date=April 29, 2013 | accessdate=August 26, 2014}}</ref><!-- also confirmed by ADV episode -->\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[Gasaraki]]'